text: Mesnil-Roc'h () is a commune in the Ille-et-Vilaine department in Brittany in northwestern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Saint-Pierre-de-Plesguen (the seat), Lanhélin and Tressé.Arrêté préfectoral 11 December 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Ille-et-Vilaine department ==References== Category:Communes of Ille-et-Vilaine Category:States and territories established in 2019
title: Mesnil-Roc'h
